2025/12/15 01:06:29 INFO dspy.teleprompt.gepa.gepa: Iteration 13: Proposed new text for generate_answer.predict: ## Task Instructions

Predict Iris Species Based on Petal and Sepal Dimensions

## Task Description
Predict the species of an iris flower based on the dimensions of its petals and sepals. The task requires analyzing the input data to determine whether the iris belongs to the setosa, versicolor, or virginica species.

## Input Format
Input data will be provided in the following format:

- petal_length (float): The length of the iris petal in cm.
- petal_width (float): The width of the iris petal in cm.
- sepal_length (float): The length of the iris sepal in cm.
- sepal_width (float): The width of the iris sepal in cm.

## Niche and Domain-Specific Factual Information
The task is based on a real-world classification problem using the Iris dataset, a multiclass classification problem that is commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The dataset consists of three species of iris flowers (setosa, versicolor, and virginica) and four features (sepal length, sepal width, petal length, and petal width). The species are classified based on their average characteristics, which are summarized below:

- Setosa (Iris setosa):
  - Average sepal length: 5.1 - 7.3 cm
  - Average sepal width: 2.1 - 4.5 cm
  - Average petal length: 1.4 - 2.9 cm
  - Average petal width: 0.1 - 1.8 cm
- Versicolor (Iris versicolor):
  - Average sepal length: 5.9 - 7.9 cm
  - Average sepal width: 2.7 - 4.5 cm
  - Average petal length: 1.8 - 3.2 cm
  - Average petal width: 0.2 - 1.5 cm
- Virginica (Iris virginica):
  - Average sepal length: 6.3 - 7.9 cm
  - Average sepal width: 2.9 - 4.5 cm
  - Average petal length: 2.1 - 3.5 cm
  - Average petal width: 1.1 - 1.8 cm

## Task Evaluation Metrics
The task will evaluate the performance of the assistant based on the accuracy of the predicted species.

## Task Objective
The objective of this task is to predict the species of an iris flower based on the dimensions of its petals and sepals.

## Task Requirements
- Analyze the input data to determine the species of the iris flower.
- Use the average characteristics of each species to make a prediction.
- Provide the predicted species and explain the reasoning behind the prediction.

## Task Evaluation
The task will evaluate the performance of the assistant based on the accuracy of the predicted species. The accuracy will be calculated as the number of correctly predicted species divided by the total number of input data.

## Task Outcome
The task will provide the predicted species and the explanation of the reasoning behind the prediction, along with the evaluation metric (accuracy).
