The Iris dataset was originally created by Sir Ronald Fisher in 1936 and consists of 50 samples from each of three species of Iris flowers (Iris setosa, Iris versicolor, and Iris virginica). The dataset has since become a standard dataset in machine learning and is widely used for benchmarking and testing the performance of classification algorithms. The Iris dataset is characterized by four features:
